description: Rules for all FastAPI backend code
globs: "backend/**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---

## FastAPI conventions

- Route handlers must be async and thin — no business logic in routers
- All business logic lives in `backend/app/services/`
- Return Pydantic response schemas — never return ORM models directly
- Use `Depends()` for all RBAC checks — never check roles inline
- Use `select(Column1, Column2)` — never `select(Model)` (no `SELECT *`)
- All DB access via `AsyncSession` from `Depends(get_db)`
- Raise `HTTPException` with structured body: `{"detail": "...", "code": "..."}`

## Service class pattern

```python
class MyService:
    def __init__(self, db: AsyncSession):
        self.db = db

    async def my_method(self, ...) -> MyResponseSchema:
        ...
```

## LLM calls

- Use `LLMService.chat_stream()` for conversational (thread/chat) calls
- Use `LLMService.chat_structured(output_schema=...)` for structured generation
- Never call provider SDKs (openai, anthropic) directly
- Never parse LLM output with regex or string splitting

## File downloads

- Always `StreamingResponse` from MinIO — never presigned URLs

## Yjs persistence

- Always dual-write: `yjs_state` (BYTEA binary) + `content` (plain text)
- Never write only `content` — this destroys CRDT state
